 not exclusively, since April. Stelter will <i>not</i> reprise his previous=
 role as anchor of a Sunday media show, but he will return to the helm of t=
he Reliable Sources newsletter that he launched
in 2015 and made into an essential nightly digest for media insiders=E2=80=
=94and, coincidentally, posing a considerable challenge to his erstwhile un=
derstudy, <b>Oliver Darcy</b>, who recently busted out of CNN to start a Re=
liable clone and competitor. Befitting the new economics of both media and =
television, Stelter will make a fraction of his previous salary.<br/><br/>U=
nsurprisingly, Stelter=E2=80=99s homecoming raised <i>a lot</i> of question=
s among the media insiders to whom he caters. Originally a mild-mannered TV=
