 2022, then-C.E.O. <b>Chris Licht </b>told his boss <b>David Zaslav </b>tha=
t he was going to fire Stelter. Sources present at the time disagree about =
whether Zaz had delicately encouraged Licht to reach that decision, or whet=
her Licht naively thought it was the best way to fulfill Zaz=E2=80=99s depo=
larization mandate. Zaz has professed to like Stelter personally since earl=
y in his career, when he took the then-22 year old to his first meal at the=
 Four Seasons. In any event, Zaz did not intervene in Licht=E2=80=99s decis=
ion. But he <i>did</i> send warm missives to Stelter on his way out the doo=
r and continued to stay in touch with him while he was in the wilderness. O=
n one Instagram post during Stelter=E2=80=99s
